ow available. Like many medieval texts for the use of magicians, this handbook is a miscellany rather than a systematic treatise. It is exceptional, however, in the scope and variety of its contents—prayers and conjurations, rituals of sympathetic magic, procedures involving astral magic, a catalogue of spirits, lengthy ceremonies for consecrating a book of magic, and other materials. With more detail on particular experiments than the famous thirteenth-century Picatrix and more variety than the Thesaurus Necromantiae ascribed to Roger Bacon, the manual is one of the most interesting and important manuscripts of medieval magic that has yet come to light.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aBODY, MIND & SPIRIT / Magick Studies.2bisacsh  aA Necromancer's Manual of the Fifteenth Century.  aBavarian State Library.  aEuropean.  aHistory.  aMagic in History.  aMunich.  aPicatrix.  aRichard Kieckhefer.  aRoger Bacon.  aThesaurus Necromatiae.  aastral magic.  abook of magic.  acatalogue of spirits.  aceremonies.  acommentary.  acomparison.  aconjurations.  aconsecrating.  adetailed analysis.  ahistorical context.  alate Middle Ages.  amagicians.  amedieval Latin text.  aprayers.  arituals.  asympathetic magic.  atranslation.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978027106544140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271065441423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271065441/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK